Package: tenbox
Version: @VERSION@
Section: admin
Priority: optional
Architecture: @ARCH@
Maintainer: as.nssai.com <contact@nssai.com>
Homepage: https://tenbox.ai
Pre-Depends: adduser
Depends: libc6 (>= 2.31),
 ca-certificates
Suggests: qemu-utils
Description: TenBox virtualization daemon and CLI
 TenBox is a single-host VM monitor with cloud-managed remote desktop.
 The daemon talks to KVM directly through /dev/kvm and ships its own
 virtio devices, qcow2 backend, and user-mode network stack, so it
 does NOT fork qemu-system-*. This package ships the headless daemon
 (tenboxd), the per-VM runtime (agentsphere-vm-runtime) and the local CLI
 (tenbox). FFmpeg / libx264 / libopus / libyuv / libcurl / OpenSSL are
 statically linked and libstdc++ / libgcc are baked in via
 -static-libstdc++ / -static-libgcc, so the only runtime requirements
 are the system libc (>= 2.31) and ca-certificates. qemu-utils (for
 qemu-img) is only needed when building custom rootfs templates with
 the helper scripts in scripts/, so it is suggested rather than
 required. A single deb installs cleanly across Debian 11+/12+/13+,
 Ubuntu 20.04+/22.04+/24.04+, Raspberry Pi OS 11+/12, and Armbian
 Bullseye+/Bookworm; dropping the libssl3 / libssl3t64 OR-dep is what
 lets bullseye (libssl1.1 only) install the same artifact as trixie
 (libssl3t64).
